'From Squeak 2.5 of August 6, 1999 on 20 August 1999 at 4:11:32 pm'!"Change Set:		explore-bfDate:			20 August 1999Author:			Bert FreudenbergA little polishing for Bob's ObjectExplorer:	- special case OrderedCollections, Dictionaries and FloatArrays like the Inspector does	- let Floats be atomic	- show multi-line values in one line"!!Dictionary methodsFor: 'testing' stamp: 'bf 8/20/1999 15:07'!hasContentsInExplorer	^self isEmpty not! !!Float methodsFor: 'testing' stamp: 'bf 8/20/1999 12:56'!hasContentsInExplorer	^false! !!ObjectExplorerWrapper methodsFor: 'as yet unclassified' stamp: 'bf 8/20/1999 10:24'!asString	| s |	s _ itemName , ': ' , item asExplorerString.	(s includes: Character cr) ifTrue: [ s _ s withSeparatorsCompacted].	^s! !!ObjectExplorerWrapper methodsFor: 'as yet unclassified' stamp: 'bf 8/20/1999 14:00'!contents	| answer |	answer _ OrderedCollection new.	({OrderedCollection. FloatArray. Dictionary} contains: [:class | item isKindOf: class])		ifTrue: [			item keysAndValuesDo: [:key :value |				answer add: (ObjectExplorerWrapper					with: value					name: (key printString contractTo: 32)					model: item)]]		ifFalse: [			item class allInstVarNames asArray doWithIndex: [:each :index |				answer add: (ObjectExplorerWrapper					with: (item instVarAt: index)					name: each					model: item)].			1 to: item basicSize do: [:index |				answer add: (ObjectExplorerWrapper					with: (item basicAt: index)					name: index printString					model: item)]].	^ answer! !!OrderedCollection methodsFor: 'testing' stamp: 'bf 8/20/1999 15:08'!hasContentsInExplorer	^self isEmpty not! !